modules.description: Provides methods to access device orientation data, including compass heading and rotation angles. Works with numeric values representing degrees and acceleration vectors. Enables real-time tracking of device movement for applications like augmented reality interfaces.

Provides functions to create heading options, extract magnetic and true heading values, retrieve heading accuracy and timestamp, and handle errors. Works with custom types representing heading data, error objects, and configuration options. Used to fetch the current device heading and continuously monitor heading changes with specified update frequency.
